  %p He graduated at Faculty of Electrical Engineering and Information Technologies in Skopje, Macedonia at 9th of October, 2007. Diploma work was titled "B2C application in J2EE platform" and it was including implementation of practical B2C (Business to Consumer) model application using J2EE (Java 2 Enterprise Edition) platform.

  %p After the studies he was working as a Computer Engineer for Stopanska Banka (largest bank in Macedonia) and Libra 1 (very large wholesale pharmaceutical company in Macedonia) for about half a year.

  %p In this period his personal interests in programming languages and technologies have slightly changed. Java stuff including JSP, Struts, Tiles, EJB, Hibernate, etc... were left behind for the benefit of more productive technologies like Ruby Programming Language and Ruby on Rails web application framework.

  %p Starting from May 2008, he was employed by <a href="http://www.aspekt.com.mk">Aspekt</a> and worked as Solution Designer / Senior Web Developer bringing and implementing new technologies and ideas into the company. This job also includes few offshore outsourcing projects for a very popular online gaming company.

